<chapter title="Introduction" file="Introduction">

<cite>ProcText</cite> provides versatile and configurable text processing and manipulation facilities, based on a set of pre-programmed actions and a user-configurable search and replace facility.

In addition to this manual, interactive help is fully supported.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Installing ProcText" file="Install">

To install <cite>ProcText</cite>, drag the <file>!ProcText</file> application directory from the archive to a suitable location on your hard disc. Once copied, <cite>ProcText</cite> can be started by double-clicking in the usual way.

<cite>ProcText</cite> is 26/32-bit neutral, and should therefore run on all hardware systems as long as the 32-bit Shared C Library is installed. If required, this can be found in the System Resources on RISC&nbsp;OS Open Ltd&rsquo;s website at <link ref="https://www.riscosopen.org/content/downloads/common">https://www.riscosopen.org/content/downloads/common</link>.

</chapter>



<chapter title="Using ProcText" file="Use">

Once installed on disc, <cite>ProcText</cite> can be started in the usual way by double-clicking on its application directory to place a copy on the iconbar.


</chapter>



